title: Autonomous Republic of Crimea
summary: The Autonomous Republic of Crimea (Ukrainian: Автономна Республіка Крим, Avtonomna Respublika Krym; Russian: Автономная Республика Крым, Avtonomnaya Respublika Krym; Crimean Tatar: Qırım Muhtar Cumhuriyeti) is de jure an autonomous republic of Ukraine encompassing most of Crimea that was annexed by Russia in 2014.
